acceptData(Object) - Method in class curam.util.client.domain.convert.AbstractConverter
Indicates if the plug-in will accept the given data for processing. It is up to the plug-in to decide what data it will accept. This method is called by the system before any processing methods of the specific types of supported plug-ins are called. Those processing methods will not be called if the data is not accepted, so this method allows the other methods on this plug-in to be written with the minimum of safety checks.

This implementation accepts all data without any checks. Overrides the basic implementation to reject any null data or data whose type is not assignable to the class returned by the DomainConverter.getDomainClass() method.

acceptData(Object) - Method in class curam.util.client.view.AbstractComponentRenderer
Indicates if the plug-in will accept the given data for processing. It is up to the plug-in to decide what data it will accept. This method is called by the system before any processing methods of the specific types of supported plug-ins are called. Those processing methods will not be called if the data is not accepted, so this method allows the other methods on this plug-in to be written with the minimum of safety checks.

This implementation accepts all data without any checks. Overrides the inherited implementation to reject all null data and all data that is not a Component object.
